{"eventId": "evt_4f5a6b7c8d", "eventType": "sentence_first_seen", "claimId": "clm_mc_001", "fromRevisionId": 1280000071, "toRevisionId": 1280000072, "section": "Combat", "before": "", "after": "As of Java Edition 1.21, the mace weapon was introduced with a unique 'density' enchantment that increases damage based on fall distance, scaling up to 12.5 hearts per block fallen.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "The mace weapon entry first appeared in this wiki revision.", "detail": "Added by user CraftBench, cited from minecraft.net article 'Tricky Trials Update' (June 2024)."}, {"fact": "The damage formula '12.5 hearts per block fallen' was transcribed directly from the official patch notes."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-06-15T12:22:45Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_5a6b7c8d9e", "eventType": "sentence_removed", "claimId": "clm_mc_002", "fromRevisionId": 1280000073, "toRevisionId": 1280000074, "section": "Crafting", "before": "The Netherite upgrade requires a Smithing Table and a Netherite Ingot. Place the diamond tool in the left slot and the Netherite Ingot in the right slot.", "after": "", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "The old-style Netherite upgrade recipe (two-slot Smithing Table) was removed from the page.", "detail": "Removed by moderator BlockBench following the 1.20 update which changed the Smithing Table to require a Netherite Upgrade Smithing Template in addition to the ingot."}, {"fact": "The removal was part of a coordinated wiki cleanup to deprecate pre-1.20 crafting recipes across all tool and armor pages."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-07-03T09:45:11Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_6b7c8d9e0f", "eventType": "sentence_modified", "claimId": "clm_mc_003", "fromRevisionId": 1280000075, "toRevisionId": 1280000076, "section": "Mobs", "before": "The Warden is a powerful hostile mob found in the Deep Dark biome, with a ranged sonic boom attack.", "after": "The Warden is the strongest hostile mob in Minecraft, found exclusively in the Deep Dark biome. Its sonic boom attack bypasses all armor and shields, deals 15 hearts of damage on Hard difficulty, and has a range of 20 blocks\u2014making it the only mob capable of killing a fully enchanted Netherite player in two hits.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "The Warden's description was expanded from basic identification to quantitative threat assessment.", "detail": "Damage values (15 hearts), range (20 blocks), and armor-bypass mechanics were added from in-game testing data compiled by the Minecraft Wiki community."}, {"fact": "The claim 'strongest hostile mob' was added with supporting comparison data against the Ender Dragon and Wither.", "detail": "A table comparing Warden vs. Wither vs. Ender Dragon stats was linked in a footnote."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-08-12T15:33:07Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_7c8d9e0f1a", "eventType": "section_reorganized", "claimId": null, "fromRevisionId": 1280000077, "toRevisionId": 1280000078, "section": "Villager Trading", "before": "(Trading mechanics were interleaved with individual villager profession descriptions throughout the page)", "after": "(A unified 'Trading Mechanics' section was created consolidating the trading economy rebalance changes from versions 1.20.2 through 1.21)", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "Trading information previously spread across 12 profession-specific subsections was consolidated into a single 'Trading Mechanics' H2 section.", "detail": "The reorganization was prompted by the 1.20.2 Villager Trade Rebalance experimental feature, which fundamentally changed how enchanting books are obtained from Librarians."}, {"fact": "A compatibility matrix was added documenting which trade tables apply under the rebalance toggle vs. legacy mode.", "detail": "This addressed frequent editor confusion about which prices to list on profession pages."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-09-01T11:20:44Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_8d9e0f1a2b", "eventType": "revert_detected", "claimId": "clm_mc_004", "fromRevisionId": 1280000079, "toRevisionId": 1280000080, "section": "Enchanting", "before": "The maximum enchantment level for Efficiency is V (5), obtainable via an enchanting table or anvil combination.", "after": "The maximum enchantment level for Efficiency is V (5), obtainable via an enchanting table or anvil combination.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "Revision 1280000079 was a revert of revision 1280000078.", "detail": "An anonymous editor had changed the max Efficiency level to 'VI (6)' with a note claiming 'possible with commands'. The revert by moderator BlockBench noted: 'rv misinformation \u2014 /give can produce any level but that is not survival-legal. The page documents legitimate gameplay.'"}, {"fact": "The revert restored the survival-gameplay-legal maximum of Efficiency V.", "detail": "Creative/commands-only mechanics are documented on a separate 'Cheats and Commands' page per wiki policy."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-09-28T17:55:30Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_9e0f1a2b3c", "eventType": "sentence_modified", "claimId": "clm_mc_005", "fromRevisionId": 1280000081, "toRevisionId": 1280000082, "section": "Crafting", "before": "The Crafting Table provides a 3x3 crafting grid, enabling the creation of most items in the game.", "after": "The Crafting Table provides a 3x3 crafting grid required for all non-inventory recipes. As of Java Edition 1.21, it also serves as a workstation block for the Crafter villager profession (new in 1.21) and accepts redstone signal input to lock output slots.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "The base description was retained but expanded with the Crafter profession and redstone mechanics from 1.21.", "detail": "The Crafter villager profession and redstone-locking behavior were both introduced in the 1.21 Tricky Trials update (June 2024)."}, {"fact": "The phrase 'most items' was replaced with the more precise 'all non-inventory recipes'.", "detail": "This reflects that the 2x2 inventory grid is sufficient for some basic recipes (planks, sticks, etc.), while the 3x3 grid is required for everything else."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-10-15T10:12:33Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_0f1a2b3c4d", "eventType": "sentence_first_seen", "claimId": "clm_mc_006", "fromRevisionId": 1280000083, "toRevisionId": 1280000084, "section": "World Generation", "before": "", "after": "Java Edition 1.21 introduced Trial Chambers, procedurally generated underground structures containing trial spawners that scale enemy count based on the number of nearby players. Each chamber contains between 12-20 spawners and 2-4 vault blocks.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "Trial Chambers were documented for the first time on the World Generation page.", "detail": "Added with direct citations to Minecraft 1.21 changelog and the Minecraft Wiki's own in-game testing data."}, {"fact": "The spawner scaling mechanic ('scale enemy count based on the number of nearby players') was confirmed via community decompilation analysis.", "detail": "This mechanic had been discovered by the technical Minecraft community and verified against decompiled 1.21 source."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-11-03T14:28:19Z"}
{"eventId": "evt_1a2b3c4d5f", "eventType": "talk_thread_opened", "claimId": null, "fromRevisionId": 1280000085, "toRevisionId": 1280000086, "section": "Talk:Crafting", "before": "", "after": "The 1.21 snapshot 24w33a introduced the 'auto-crafting' mechanic via the Crafter block. Should we restructure the crafting page to separate 'manual crafting' from 'auto-crafting', or treat the Crafter as a sub-section of Redstone? Previous precedent: hoppers are documented under both Redstone and Item Transport.", "deterministicFacts": [{"fact": "A talk page thread titled 'Auto-crafting \u2014 separate page or Redstone sub-section?' was opened by user RedstoneEngineer.", "detail": "Posted 2024-12-05T19:22:41Z, referencing snapshot 24w33a changes."}, {"fact": "The thread notes a prior precedent: the hopper block is cross-referenced in both Redstone and Item Transport sections.", "detail": "This was cited as the likely resolution pattern for the Crafter block's documentation placement."}], "layer": "observed", "timestamp": "2024-12-05T19:22:41Z"}
